section.section:
"Applicant" does not include:
a financial institution that has loaned money or extended financing for the acquisition, development, or construction or improvements on the land that is the subject of an application;
a municipal or public corporation;
a public authority;
a public service company acting within the scope of Division I of the Public Utilities Article; or
a person who is hired or retained as an accountant, attorney, architect, engineer, land use consultant, economic consultant, real estate agent, real estate broker, traffic consultant, or traffic engineer.

text.section:
"Business entity" means:
a sole proprietorship;
a corporation;
a general partnership;
a limited partnership;
a limited liability company; or
a joint venture.

"Political action committee" means a political committee that is not:
a political party;
a central committee;
a slate; or
a political committee organized and operated by, and solely on behalf of, an individual running for any elective office or a slate.
